# PrintPDF Extension

The PrintPDF extension exports Revit sheets to PDF with configurable selection, naming, and export settings.

## How to use

### 1) Destination
- **Destination Directory**: Folder where PDFs will be saved.

### 2) What to export (Export Option)
Pick one of the supported export modes:

- **ActiveView**: Exports the currently active view (must be a sheet).
- **AllSheets**: Exports all sheets in the model.
- **CustomFilter**: Exports sheets returned by the configured custom filter.
- **ViewSet**: Exports sheets from a selected Revit view/sheet set.
- **ViewCollection**: Exports sheets from a selected Revit sheet collection.
- **UseRegexInViewSet**: Matches view/sheet sets by regex, then exports each matched set.
- **UseRegexInViewCollections** *(Revit 2025+)*: Matches sheet collections by regex, then exports each matched collection.

#### Fields shown based on Export Option
- **Custom Filter**: Shown when `ExportOption == CustomFilter`.
- **Sheet Set**: Shown when `ExportOption == ViewSet`.
- **View collection**: Shown when `ExportOption == ViewCollection`.
- **Regex Pattern**: Shown when `ExportOption == UseRegexInViewSet` or `ExportOption == UseRegexInViewCollections`.

### 3) File naming
- **Naming Options**: Select how the file name is built.
- **Separator in File Name**: Separator used when the naming option combines multiple parts.
- **Prefix in file name (Optional)**: Text prepended to the file name.
- **Suffix in file name (Optional)**: Text appended to the file name.
- **Custom Naming Convention**: Shown when `NamingOptions == Custom`.

#### Custom Naming Convention tokens
Custom patterns support tokens in braces:
- Built-in tokens: `{SheetName}`, `{ModelName}`
- Any view/sheet parameter name: `{Discipline}`, `{Status}`, etc.

Examples:
- `{SheetName}_{Discipline}`
- `PDF_{ModelName}_{SheetName}`
- `Custom-{SheetName}-v1`

### 4) Combine output
- **Combine**: When enabled, exports each selection as a single combined PDF.
- **Use sheet set name as PDF Name**: Shown when `Combine == true`.
- **Combined File Name (Optional)**: Shown when `Combine == true` and `UseSheetSetNameAsPdfName == false`.

> Note: When exporting via regex (multiple sets/collections), each matched set/collection is exported as its own combined PDF.

### 5) PDF export settings
- **Always Use Raster**
- **Color Depth Type**
- **PDF Export Quality Type**
- **Hide Crop Boundaries**
- **Hide Reference Plane**
- **Hide Scope Boxes**
- **Hide Unreferenced View Tags**
- **Mask Coincident Lines**
- **Replace Halftone With Thin Lines**
- **View Links In Blue**
- **Origin Offset X**
- **Origin Offset Y**
- **Zoom Type**
- **Zoom Percentage**
- **Paper Format**
- **Page Orientation Type**
- **Paper Placement Type**
- **Raster Quality Type**
- **Open View On Export**

## Execution

Once configured, the extension collects sheets based on the selected **Export Option** and exports them to PDF in the configured **Destination Directory**.
